  AADDDDIINNGG PPOOLLYYHHEEDDRRAA

    If you have the source to iiccoo, you can easily add more polyhedra. Each
    polyhedron is defined in an include file by the name of oobbjjXXX..hh, where
    XXX is something related to the name of the polyhedron. The format of the
    include file is defined in the file ppoollyyiinnffoo..hh.. Look at the file oobbjjccuubbee..hh
    to see what the exact format of an oobbjjXXX..hh file should be, then create
    your oobbjjXXX..hh file in that format.

    After making the new oobbjjXXX..hh file (or copying in a new one from
    elsewhere), simply do a "make depend" operation. This will recreate the
    file aalllloobbjjss..hh, which lists all of the oobbjjXXX..hh files. Doing a "make"
    operation after this will rebuild iiccoo with the new object information.

  BBUUGGSS

    Pyramids and tetrahedrons with filled faces do not display correctly.

    A separate color cell is allocated for each name in the -colors list, even
    when the same name might be specified twice.

